deck: Pepper must learn to trust Gene when he, as the Mandarin, is trying to orchestrate a deal between the Tong and Count Nefaria's Maggia.
name: Pepper, Interrupted

deck: Tony's virus, the Technovore, fuses with Project Pegasus's nanobot project, becoming a growing threat towards SHIELD and later, the world.
name: Technovore

deck: Gene Khan's past is revealed as Tony, Pepper, and Rhodey deal with the Makluan guardian known as Firebrand.
name: World on Fire

deck: Tony Stark seeks to help a dying Living Laser. Unfortunately, Ghost kidnaps him in order to help create AIM's latest project: MODOK!
name: Designed Only for Chaos

deck: Happy Hogan takes the Iron Man suit for a joyride, just as the Tong, Killer Shrike, Unicorn, and Mr. Fix all pursue Iron Man to kill him.
name: Don't Worry, Be Happy

deck: Iron Man's "Dynamobuster" armor is used by the Controller to exact his revenge on MODOK and AIM. Only the Incredible Hulk, alongside Rick Jones, Rhodey, and Pepper, can save Tony.
name: Uncontrollable

object_credits.name: Iron Man Hulkbuster Armor Mk. I

deck: Whitney, growing increasingly insane as Madame Masque, tries to kill Obadiah Stane, and asks Tony to help him cure her. Tony must retrieve a rare ore to cure what is poisoning her mind. Stane also frees Blizzard to help him, but he has some motives of his own.
name: Best Served Cold

deck: The gang and Gene find the fifth Makluan ring and awaken the final guardian, Fin Fang Foom, just as the Tong betray Gene and set up a chain of events with high repercussions.
name: Tales of Suspense: Part 1

deck: Rhodey must don Tony's new War Machine armor to save him, Pepper, and Gene, from Fin Fang Foom and the Tong. Mysteries are answered and shocking reveals await our heroes.
name: Tales of Suspense: Part 2

deck: Tony Stark returns from retirement months after the events of the season finale when Whiplash targets young millionaire Justin Hammer.
name: The Invincible Iron Man, Part 1: Disassembled

deck: Iron Man returns with upgraded armor to aid War Machine against Whiplash, Blizzard, and Mr. Fix. Meanwhile, Howard Stark and Gene find the next Makluan ring.
name: The Invincible Iron Man, Part 2: Reborn!

deck: Cliffhanger: Batman and Robin are strapped to giant grills and large magnifying glasses are poised over them to roast them alive!
name: Hot Off the Griddle

deck: Thanks to a timely solar eclipse, the dynamic duo are given the time they need to use their feet and adjust the giant magnifying glasses to melt their straps.
name: The Cat and the Fiddle

deck: It's a history lesson with the Fantastic Four.
description:
With the Invisible Woman in Doctor Doom's grasp, the Thing, Mr. Fantastic and the Human Torch are forced to travel back in time. Once there, the three have to join a war between Greeks and Persians. Their objective is simple: Get a Greek coffin and give it to Doom. Will Johnny Storm, Reed Richards and Ben Grimm, save Susan Storm before Doom kills her?

Note: This, including it's previous episodes are all direct adaptations of Fantastic Four Issue #5.
name: The Mask of Doom: Part 3

deck: Galactus and Doom are back for more action!
description:
It's a double threat for the team. Doctor Doom has returned after their time travelling treasure hunt in the previous episodes with Galactus, who is once again trying to consume Earth. The Silver Surfer also joins the fun, but he is feeling powerless at the moment when Doom obtained the Power Cosmic from him. Doom, with a large amount of power at his side, is out to rule the Earth while Galactus tries to satisfy his galactic hunger. It's all up to the Fantastic Four to save the world!

Note 1: This is the first season's finale.

Note 2: This is one of two episodes of the first season to not be an issue adaptation. The other being "Behold the Negative Zone".

Note 3: This episode has a vague similarity towards Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer's plot where in the Surfer's powers are also taken.

Note 4: This episode will inspire the series's finale titled "Doomsday".

Note 5: In a particular scene in this episode, there is a computer screen or holographic projection in the background. The projection shows Iron Man, War Machine and Ultimo doing battle against each other. This is a clear reference to another Marvel Action Hour program (the other being this show and The Incredible Hulk: Animated Series), which is the Iron Man: Animated Series episode "Rejoice! I am Ultimo, Thy Deliverer", which also featured the three characters in the same plot.

Sub-Note 5.5: Since neither Iron Man, Ultimo and War Machine appeared in physical form ,they are not categorized as characters in the series, and therefore, they did not technically appear in this episode.
name: The Silver Surfer and the Return of Galactus

deck: Mole Man takes a New York landmark underground.
description:
When a dwarf-like villain named Mole Man, a ruler of an underground kingdom, takes Rockefeller Tower downward in order to destroy the Fantastic Four. Mole Man takes the citizens hostage and a challenge to the surface dwellers. The Fantastic Four must make a daring trek towards Mole Man's underground lair and beat up a huge pack of Moloids (Subterraneans) to save the people before all is lost.

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation of Fantastic Four Issue #1.
name: Mole Man

deck: It's a home invasion in the Baxter Building!
description:
Reed Richards had an argument with their landlady. While they were arguing about payment, the device that is used to enter the Negative Zone has been activated and the portal has been unleashed. Two inhabitants of the dimension, Blastaar and Annhilus, have escaped the Negative Zone. They are planning to rule the world (as every villain wants) and have to fight the Fantastic Four to get it.

Note: This is one of two episodes of the first season that has an original script instead of an adaptation. The other being "The Silver Surfer and the Return of Galactus".
name: Behold the Negative Zone

deck: Daredevil helps the team in getting their powers back.
description:
The Fantastic Four are lured into a Doombot-filled island. Doctor Doom escapes and the team are able to rescue the trapped Susan Storm. Doom activates a bomb that will go off any second, and just when they were about to escape, Doom destroys their ride and the bomb explodes. The next day, the Navy were able to rescue and they wake up to find their powers missing. Alicia Masters asked the aid of Matt Murdock to guide the team. With the help from Daredevil, the Fantastic Four must get their powers back from Doom.

Note 1: This episode is a direct adaptation and combination of Fantastic Four Issues #39 and #40.

Note 2: This marks as the second season's first episode.
name: And A Blind Man Shall Lead Them

deck: The mark of the Frightful Four!
description:
The Fantastic Four comes face-to-face with the vicious, Frightful Four. A sinister counterpart of the team, they carry the combined might of Hydro-Man, Wizard, Medusa and Trapster. The team's leader, Wizard, was able to mind-control Thing and force him against his will to destroy the team, including his best friend, Reed. This is the beginning of Season 2's monumental story arc, with three parts.

Note 1: This episode is a direct adaptation and combination of Fantastic Four Issues #36, #41, #42 and #43.

Note 2: Similar to Spider-Man: The Animated Series, the Sandman was absent. He was suppose to be one of the members of the Frightful Four. This is because James Cameron was planning to make a Spider-Man movie (but was scrapped), which features the Sandman and Electro, who were suppose to be the main villains (This was also the reason why Electro was missing in Spider-Man: The Animated Series. Until it was revealed that the film's version was also not that the mainstream counterpart that they made Electro's debut in Season 5, even though he is still not similar to the comics version).
name: Inhumans Saga Part 1: And The Wind Cries Medusa

deck: Who is Gorgon and why is he chasing Medusa?
description:
Human Torch is really tired of being treated like a kid, so he sets out on his own. While wondering the streets of New York, he encounters Medusa, who is running away from Gorgon, who is chasing her for unknown circumstances. Johnny and the others intervene and Gorgon escaped. Afterwards, a mysterious race known as the Inhumans meet Johnny. He later learns about Crystal and later fights Black Bolt, while being backed-up by the team.

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation and combination of Fantastic Four Issues #44 and #45.
name: Inhumans Saga Part 2: The Inhumans Among Us

Flashback episode.

deck: The corrupt Box County officials try to impound the proceeds from the sale of the gold, Jeff Stewart smuggled out of the county, but when Stewart turns it over to the U.S. Postal Service, he's arrested for violating a County Court Order.
name: Fugitive from Injustice

name: Rebellion

description: The Decepticons have a plan to clone dead Predacons.
name: Project Predacon

description: Cragger is caught stealing the powerful Chi, the Lions - keepers of the chi, call the King and Queen of the Croc Tribe which results in a misunderstanding which lead into an all out war.
name: Legends of Chima

description: At the Chi day festival in Lion City during the races Cragger attacks together with the Wolves and the Ravens. The Lions call in the help of their friends - the Eagle and Gorilla Tribes, and all learn a viable lesson in peace.
name: The Great Story

description: Laval withholds Chi from the Croc Tribe on the advice of Cragger. This almost sets off another war. Can Laval escape the Croc Tribe and the wrath of his father?
name: The Warrior Within

description: Cragger has employed the help of the Beaver Tribe to steel the Chi he's so desperately looking for. Laval and Eris are on a trip around Chima, will they be in time to stop Cragger?
name: The Joy Ride

description: Laval and Eris head to the market at the montly Speedor races. Meanwhile Cragger gets some help from the Raven Tribe to steel Laval's speedor. Some time later the prize of the races, the Golden Chi, also gets stolen.
name: Market Day

description: The Croc Tribe hire the Raven Tribe to trick the Wolf Tribe into attacking the Eagle Spires. Laval and Eris find out that it's all a trap to harm them all, they must be quick to save the day.
name: Attack on Eagle Spire

description: The Wolf Tribe run wild and cause havoc at the night of the Hundred Year Moon. Crooler the crocodile kidnaps a young Gorilla girl.
name: The Hundred Year Moon

description: The biggest orb of Golden Chi is up for grabs at the biggest of all races. Cragger has hired the best Speedor driver of Chima to win the Chi for him, but another rider, one that no-one knows also enters the race.
name: The Biggest Race of All

description: The Gorilla Tribe have had enough of Craggers stunts and trash to the swamp to teach him a lesson. But they're too big and sink in the swampy water, so much so that the Lions and Eagles have to come to their rescue. Only problem is that Lions are afraid of the water.
name: Gorilla's Gone Wild

description: Crooler, with the help of the Wolf Tribe tries to steal all of the Chi from the Lion Temple. Then Shadowind shows up again.
name: Foxtrot

description: The lions are upset, they can't get the Chi to the other tribes because the Wolf Tribe keeps stealing it. Because they're now using more Chi they're getting stronger and are harder to keep at bay. It's up to Eris and Laval to find a Wolf proof way of getting the Chi to the other tribes.
name: The Chi Jackers

description: There's no stopping the Wolves from stealing the Chi that is meant for the other tribes. At one Chi run the precious load of Chi plunges into the Gorge of Eternal Depth. The Chi is so scarce that even Cragger joins the team of Eris, Laval and Gorzan to get the Chi back.
name: Balancing Act

description: The Croc Tribe - lead by Cragger, attacks the Wolves in an attempt to take back the Chi they've stolen, but things go wrong and the Crocodiles are taken prisoner. When Lavel hears about it he's determined to resque Cragger and the rest.
name: Crocodile Tears

description: Crooler loses control over her brother Cragger, he reverts to his old self and is trying to help everyone that needs it.
name: Fake Chi, Real Trouble

description: The Raven Tribe takes advantage of Laval and Cragger's absence and moves into Eagle Spires. The Eagles try to get rid of them but the Ravens won't leave. Eris will have to think of something to make them leave.
name: Ravens vs. Eagles

description: There's a peace conference going on on Chima, but Crooler is trying to interfere.
name: Reunion Gone Wrong

description: The Lion Tribe King Lagravis exiled his son Laval for fighting at the peace conference. While he's in exile he hears his father has been imprisoned by Cragger.
name: Laval in Exile

description: A black cloud decends on Mt. Cavora, which is the source of all the Chi. Laval and Eris investigate but the cloud stops them at every turn.
name: The Black Cloud

description: The Chi waterfalls running down from Mount Cavora have run dry and Eris and the Beaver Tribe are trying to find out why. The Croc Tribe blame the Lion Tribe and rally all their befriended tribes around them to take the last of the Chi by force.
name: Chima Falls

description: The Chi falls are still dry and the black cloud is still hanging around Mount Cavora. Down below at the Lion Temple the fight is on, can the Lions hang out long enough for Laval to find a peaceful solution?
name: For Chima!

description: Tension build between Wheeljack and Ultra Magnus.
name: Chain of Command

name: Plus One

description: KnockOut and Starscream accidentally create a threat from their experiments.
name: Thirst

description: Predaking reveals his ability to transform to the Decepticons.
name: Evolution

name: Minus One

description: Megatron kidnaps Ratchet, and offers him something they both want. The Resurrection of Cybertron.
name: Persuasion

description: Team Prime attempt to rescue Ratchet from the Decepticons.
name: Synthesis
